The paper discusses a new computation paradigm for exploratory data analysis, which involves performing computations in a progressive fashion to ensure low-latency feedback for the analyst. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including databases (cs.DB) for managing and querying large datasets, human-computer interaction (cs.HC) for designing user interfaces that support data exploration, information retrieval (cs.IR) for searching and analyzing large amounts of data, machine learning (cs.LG) for developing scalable algorithms for data analysis, and software engineering (cs.SE) for designing and implementing data analysis systems.
